result.execSummary:
The defendant Jasmine R. Wastlick was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 15A 000211 - BAIL FORFEITURE ORDERED BY THE COURT DURING SENTENCING

Defendant Jasmine R. Wastlick in court, in custody, with attorney David William Franker. Prosecuting Atty Amy Forehand appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Called together:  14CM91, 14CM184, 15CM5, 14CM119, 14CM125, 14CM127, 14CM147.  

Court completes the initial appearances in 15CM5 and 14CM184.  Formal readings waived.  Charges and possible max. penalties stated.

ADA Forehand states that the parties have reached an agreement whereby def will enters pleas of GNC to:
14CM91 - dc and resisting charges
14CM119 - dc charge
14CM127 - 1 bail jumping charge
14CM184 - 1 bail jumping charge
15CM5 - dc and 1 count bail jumping
All other counts in these cases and any other cases to be dismissed/read in. Jt recommendation calls for forfeiting of $4150 bond in 15CM5; ADA agrees not to file a motion to forfeit all other cash bond.
14CM184 - sentence recommendation is for straight sentence of 90 days jail
On all other cases, the sentence recommendation is for probation for 2 years with conditions of costs, AODA/follow through, psych. evaluation/follow through, no alcohol, no taverns, no contact with GK.

Atty. Franker concurs with ADA Forehand's recitation of the agreement.

Def pleads no contest to the charges stated in the parties' agreement.  All enhancers have been dismissed.  Def's pleas are for the counts without enhancers.  Court's colloquy re pleas.  Finding of guilty.  

Counsel address the Court.  Atty. Franker states that def should be entitled to 50 days credit in 14CM184; also asks for stay of jail until 2/13/15.

Court rules on sentence:  
$4150 ordered forfeited in 15CM5 but other cash bails to be returned after application of court costs.
14CM184 - 90 days jail with 50 days credit.  Jail stayed until Friday, Feb. 13, 2015 between 6-7 a.m.  Work release granted.
All other cases:  Sentence withheld for 2 years probation, terms concurrent, with conditions that def pay costs excluding DNA surcharges, submit to AODA/follow through, psych. eval and follow through, no possess/consumption of alcohol, no bars/taverns or any places engaged in primary sale of alcohol, no contact with GK, testing on demand by leo or prob. officer to monitor compliance.

Attorney David W. Franker appeared by phone means for Defendant Jasmine R. Wastlick. Prosecuting Atty Amy Forehand appeared for State of Wisconsin.
14CM184/adjourned initial
14CM91, 14CM147, 14CM127, 14CM125, and 14CM119/status
15CM5/initial
Def is in jail.  Atty. Franker requests adjournment of all matters to next date he is here - Feb. 11 at 1:30.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for February 11, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
